---
import CalculatorLayout from '../../../layouts/CalculatorLayout.astro';
import Formula from '../../../components/Formula.astro';

const f = {
  fwd: "$$\\text{st} = \\text{kg} \\div 6.35029$$",
  rev: "$$\\text{kg} = \\text{st} \\times 6.35029$$",
};

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'how-to-use',      label: 'How to use this converter' },
  { id: 'formula',         label: 'How to convert kg to stone' },
  { id: 'reverse',         label: 'How to convert stone to kg' },
  { id: 'reference-table', label: 'kg to stone reference table' },
  { id: 'when-to-use',     label: 'When you need this conversion' },
  { id: 'faq',             label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'related-tools',   label: 'Related tools' },
];

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "Kilograms to Stone Converter",
    "url": "https://calculations.tools/conversion/weight-converter/kg-to-st",
    "description": "Convert kilograms to stone instantly. Formula: st = kg ÷ 6.35029. Includes reverse stone to kg conversion and a body weight reference table.",
    "applicationCategory": "UtilitiesApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Any",
    "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
    "isAccessibleForFree": true,
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many stone is 70 kg?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "70 kg equals 11.023 stone. Divide 70 by 6.35029: 70 ÷ 6.35029 = 11.023 st." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you convert kg to stone?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Divide kilograms by 6.35029. Example: 80 kg ÷ 6.35029 = 12.598 st. Quick estimate: divide by 6.35." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many stone is 60 kg?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "60 kg equals 9.449 stone. Divide 60 by 6.35029: 60 ÷ 6.35029 = 9.449 st." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many stone is 100 kg?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "100 kg equals 15.747 stone. Divide 100 by 6.35029: 100 ÷ 6.35029 = 15.747 st." }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<CalculatorLayout
  title="Kilograms to Stone Converter"
  metaTitle="Kilograms to Stone Converter | kg to st ᐅ"
  description="Convert kilograms to stone instantly. Formula: st = kg ÷ 6.35029. Body weight reference table - 50 kg, 70 kg, 90 kg in stone and more."
  canonical="https://calculations.tools/conversion/weight-converter/kg-to-st"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  embedSlug="kg-to-st"
  schema={schema}
  ogFormula="st = kg ÷ 6.35029"
  ogExample="70 kg = 11.02 st"
>

  <div slot="calculator">
    <section class="calculator-interface">
      <div class="calculator-container">

        <div class="calculator-header">
          <h2>Instant Kilogram to Stone (kg to st) Calculator</h2>
          <p>Type in either field - converts instantly in both directions</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pair-inputs">
          <div class="pair-field">
            <label for="lp-a">Kilograms (kg)</label>
            <input id="lp-a" type="text" inputmode="decimal" placeholder="e.g. 70" />
          </div>
          <div class="pair-eq">=</div>
          <div class="pair-field">
            <label for="lp-b">Stone (st)</label>
            <input id="lp-b" type="text" inputmode="decimal" placeholder="e.g. 11.02" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pair-formula-note">1 kg = 0.157473 st &nbsp;·&nbsp; 1 st = 6.35029 kg</div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <script src="/js/kg-to-st.js" is:inline></script>
  </div>

  <div slot="content">
    <div class="seo-container">

      <div class="answer-box">
        <div class="answer-box-label">Quick answer</div>
        <p>To convert kilograms to stone, divide by <strong>6.35029</strong>. So 70 kg = 11.02 st and 80 kg = 12.60 st. One stone = 14 lb = 6.35029 kg exactly (derived from the 1959 pound definition).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer-box">
        <div class="answer-box-label">Key takeaways</div>
        <ul>
          <li>1 st = 6.35029 kg = 14 lb (exact from the pound definition).</li>
          <li>60 kg = 9.45 st. 70 kg = 11.02 st. 80 kg = 12.60 st.</li>
          <li>Stone is used almost exclusively in the UK and Ireland for body weight.</li>
          <li>To get whole stone and pounds: take the integer part as stone, multiply remainder by 14 to get lbs.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="how-to-use">How to Use This Converter</h2>
      <p>Type any kg value in the kg field and the stone result appears instantly. You can also type in the st field to convert back to kg. The result is in decimal stone - to convert to whole stone plus pounds, multiply the decimal part by 14.</p>

      <h2 id="formula">How Do You Convert Kilograms to Stone?</h2>
      <p>Divide kilograms by 6.35029. One stone = 14 lb exactly, and 1 lb = 0.45359237 kg, so 1 st = 6.350293... kg.</p>

      <Formula expr={f.fwd} />

      <p>Worked examples: 50 kg = 7.874 st. 60 kg = 9.449 st. 70 kg = 11.023 st. 80 kg = 12.598 st. 90 kg = 14.173 st. 100 kg = 15.747 st.</p>

      <p>To express as stone and pounds: for 70 kg = 11.023 st → 11 stone and 0.023 × 14 = 0.32 lb &asymp; 11 st 0 lb.</p>

      <h2 id="reverse">How Do You Convert Stone to Kilograms?</h2>
      <p>Multiply stone by 6.35029. See the dedicated <a href="/conversion/weight-converter/st-to-kg">stone to kilograms converter</a> for a stone-first reference table.</p>

      <Formula expr={f.rev} />

      <p>Worked examples: 10 st = 63.50 kg. 12 st = 76.20 kg. 14 st = 88.90 kg.</p>

      <h2 id="reference-table">Kilograms to Stone Reference Table</h2>
      <p>Common adult body weight values in kg converted to stone:</p>

      <div class="responsive-table">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Kilograms (kg)</th><th>Stone (st)</th><th>Stone &amp; lb</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>45 kg</td><td>7.087 st</td><td>7 st 1 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>50 kg</td><td>7.874 st</td><td>7 st 12 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>55 kg</td><td>8.661 st</td><td>8 st 9 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>60 kg</td><td>9.449 st</td><td>9 st 6 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>65 kg</td><td>10.236 st</td><td>10 st 3 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>70 kg</td><td>11.023 st</td><td>11 st 0 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>75 kg</td><td>11.811 st</td><td>11 st 11 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>80 kg</td><td>12.598 st</td><td>12 st 8 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>85 kg</td><td>13.385 st</td><td>13 st 5 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>90 kg</td><td>14.173 st</td><td>14 st 2 lb</td></tr>
            <tr><td>100 kg</td><td>15.747 st</td><td>15 st 10 lb</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 id="when-to-use">When Do You Need to Convert kg to Stone?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>UK health and NHS</strong> - clinical records use kg; UK patients often express weight in stone. Converting helps communication.</li>
        <li><strong>Fitness and diet</strong> - UK-based fitness programs, slimming clubs, and NHS weight management resources use stone.</li>
        <li><strong>UK product descriptions</strong> - weight limits on chairs, beds, and sports equipment are sometimes listed in stone in UK product specs.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How many stone is 70 kg?</h3>
      <p>70 kg = 11.023 stone = 11 stone 0 pounds (0.023 × 14 = 0.32 lb, rounds to 0). A common average adult male body weight in many countries.</p>

      <h3>How do you convert kg to stone?</h3>
      <p>Divide by 6.35029. Quick estimate: divide by 6.35 (error under 0.005%). For 75 kg: 75 ÷ 6.35 = 11.81 st (actual: 11.811 st).</p>

      <h3>How many stone is 60 kg?</h3>
      <p>60 kg = 9.449 stone = 9 stone 6 pounds (0.449 × 14 = 6.29 ≈ 6 lb).</p>

      <h3>How many stone is 100 kg?</h3>
      <p>100 kg = 15.747 stone = 15 stone 10 pounds (0.747 × 14 = 10.46 ≈ 10 lb).</p>

      <h2 id="related-tools">Related tools</h2>
      <ul class="related-tools-list">
        <li>
          <span class="tool-icon">⚖️</span>
          <div>
            <a href="/conversion/weight-converter/st-to-kg">Stone to Kilograms Converter</a>
            <p>Reverse conversion - enter stone and get kg instantly, with a stone-first reference table.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="tool-icon">⚖️</span>
          <div>
            <a href="/conversion/weight-converter/kg-to-lb">Kilograms to Pounds Converter</a>
            <p>Convert kg to lbs for US-format body weight.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="tool-icon">⚖️</span>
          <div>
            <a href="/conversion/weight-converter/lb-to-st">Pounds to Stone Converter</a>
            <p>Convert between lbs and stone within the imperial system.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="tool-icon">⚖️</span>
          <div>
            <a href="/conversion/weight-converter">Weight Converter (all units)</a>
            <p>Convert between all metric and imperial weight units simultaneously.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </div>

</CalculatorLayout>

<style is:global>
  .pair-inputs { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: end; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .pair-field label { display: block; font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
  .pair-field input { width: 100%; padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-radius: 8px; color: white; font-size: 1rem; box-sizing: border-box; }
  .pair-eq { font-size: 1.5rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); padding-bottom: 0.35rem; }
  .pair-formula-note { text-align: center; font-size: 0.75rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 480px) { .pair-inputs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .pair-eq { text-align: center; padding-bottom: 0; } }
</style>
